properties.abstract: A lovely, varied circular tour with fantastic views of the Swiss Mittelland and the Alps. Passing through Solothurn's residential areas and the sparse beech forests on the southern foot of the Jura, the physically demanding route reaches Althüsli just below the summit of the Hasenmatt. Spectacular sections along the Lochbach Gorge beckon on the descent.
properties.description:
From the baroque capital to the highest point in the canton of Solothurn. Passing St. Ursen Cathedral, the circular tour crosses Solothurn's beautiful old town. The route continues mostly on little-used side roads to Langendorf and through the Heimlisberg forest to Lommiswil. In the quarry, dinosaur tracks from over 145 million years ago can be discovered and admired from a visitor platform.

From Lommiswil onwards, pedal power is required as steeper sections follow, some with long ramps. The well-maintained mountain road leads through the sparse beech forest of the southern Jura foothills via Egg to the Althüsli mountain inn at an altitude of 1,317 metres. The Hasenmatt, the highest peak in the Canton of Solothurn at 1,445 metres above sea level, is only a stone's throw away. The 360-degree views are superb, extending from the Mittelland over the Alps, Black Forest and Vosges.

The descent to the Schauenburg mountain inn is rugged and challenging, and the Lochbachstrasse is spectacular. After the short tunnel, the views of the Mittelland lakes and the Alps open up once again. Deep down in the gorge, the Lochbach roars. A short trail leads through the Fuchsenwald forest back to Lommiswil. Follow the route past the modern Holy Spirit Church towards the Heimlisberg forest. Along the ascent trail, you return to Solothurn.
